# VLAN & Inter-VLAN Routing using Router-on-a-Stick

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of VLANs and Inter-VLAN routing using the Router-on-a-Stick technique in Cisco Packet Tracer. The network is segmented into multiple VLANs, and communication between them is enabled using router sub-interfaces with IEEE 802.1Q encapsulation.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives
- Create multiple VLANs on a Layer 2 switch
- Assign switch ports to specific VLANs
- Configure trunking between switch and router
- Implement Inter-VLAN routing using a single router interface
- Verify communication between devices in different VLANs

